TITION: The “Bare Minimum” Request to Myt</span><hr size=1> Replies from the VNboards brought up some good points:<br>
<br>
<br>
Celebwen pointed out in the counter-thread:<br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;&quot;When you try to bargain with someone (Mythic) it is always better for your cause to make several offers and let them (Mythic) choose one or maybe even two to implement.&quot;&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
Very true about the need to make several offers. Unfortunately, we aren't really bargaining, it's more like requesting. The Assassin community has ZERO bargaining power, there is nothing forcing Mythic to make any changes. But hopefully, Mythic will test out the requests in some fashion.<br>
<br>
<br>
ZiigZaag:<br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;&quot;I don't see anything wrong with these bare minimum requests. It would sure be nice to at least see them tried out on Pendragon (and of course the results of that test actually paid attention to ;p) &quot;&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
Agreed, it wouldn't hurt anyone if Mythic did actually implement all of the bare minimum requests on the Test Server. There is nothing that would force them on to the live servers. Much of the negative criticism to the petition neglects the testing portion of all changes made to classes, and post what the FEEL would happen if they went directly to the live servers.<br>
<br>
<br>
Again, you don't have to agree with everything, but for what you are in support of, please share. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujammermon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jammermon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/18/02 1:30:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1787.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: THE ASSASSIN PETITION: The “Bare Minimum” Request to Myt</span><hr size=1> I agree with a few key points;<br>
<br>
1) The Poisons do NOT ramp up the way everything else does. <br>
Given a 75% Envenom Spec; If you fight an L 20 Mob PvE or Player RvR your dot's will do 60% of the killing for you. At L30 your poisons will do about 40% of the killing for you. And by L40 its down to/below 30%. No other class has a Prime attribute carry less of a share as they level. Usually its actually a nudge more. <br>
<br>
2) Give us Parry OR Shield as passive. After the Assassin update when first logging in pop a box that says &quot;What did you practice as a Youth; &lt;Parry &lt;Shield&quot;. We clic on ONE and thats our passive skill. Then the ones who want shield can pick that and parry pick that. I would be hard pressed to decide which as Shield is very helpful quite often, but I can see we shouldn't have Parry / Shield/ and Evade. Or maybe we should... (shrugs) as at L30 with 50 Con I have 286 HP and my equal Blademaster Buddy has almost 1000. <br>
<br>
Other than that I don't think the class is quite as farqed as carried on about. BUT complete our classes! Every other toon is trotted out in a Production Version and us Assassins schlup  around in modeling clay!<br>
<br>
Jammer<br>
